Ede1 truncation blots

Experiment

Rationale

EGFP-tagged Ede1 truncation constructs expressed in wild-type or 3∆ background cells were probed by an anti-GFP antibody and an anti-Hog1 loading control. Fluorescent antibodies were used as secondaries and imaged on a LICOR Odyssey. See protocol for details; the experiment was repeated three times. It was quantified using the ImageJ gel analysis tool.
